46:14.970 --> 46:17.170
You're not a mama's boy, Peel.

46:17.172 --> 46:19.107
[♪♪♪]

46:23.177 --> 46:25.914
People think
I don't know anything.

46:28.249 --> 46:29.483
But I see things.

46:30.651 --> 46:31.586
Yeah.

46:34.355 --> 46:36.090
Yeah, I get it.

46:41.162 --> 46:44.165
And I know what happened
with Roy and Chun Ja was...

46:45.099 --> 46:46.434
It was shitty.

46:48.268 --> 46:50.638
I really don't think
he meant to hurt you.

46:52.440 --> 46:56.644
I believe him when he said
he thought it was Jooeun.

46:58.011 --> 47:00.344
And Chun Ja, she...

47:00.346 --> 47:02.015
She was wasted, man.

47:03.551 --> 47:05.385
She's into you.

47:07.488 --> 47:09.222
Don't let a silly mistake
ruin that.

47:13.527 --> 47:15.962
Roy calls me his brother.

47:18.565 --> 47:21.334
My real brothers
would've never done that.

47:24.169 --> 47:25.238
No.

47:38.485 --> 47:39.551
It's you?

47:42.688 --> 47:44.156
And your brothers?

47:47.659 --> 47:49.695
Why didn't they come
to the party?

47:51.530 --> 47:54.332
Well, I haven't seen them
in 25 years.

47:57.034 --> 47:58.969
Do you know where they are?

47:58.971 --> 48:01.206
I tried 411,
but she couldn't find them.

48:02.608 --> 48:04.006
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

48:04.008 --> 48:05.674
I don't know
what they look like,

48:05.676 --> 48:08.177
how tall they are.

48:08.179 --> 48:10.715
I don't even know
if they like to swim.

48:13.752 --> 48:15.651
Would you help me find 'em?

48:15.653 --> 48:18.455
Sure, we'll help you.

48:21.726 --> 48:23.424
You ever heard of Google?

48:23.426 --> 48:25.363
[LINE RINGING]

48:32.703 --> 48:34.502
WOMAN [ON PHONE]:
<i>Hello?</i>

48:34.504 --> 48:37.272
Could I speak to
William Munter, please?

48:37.274 --> 48:41.177
WOMAN: <i>Uh, who is this?
Do you know what time it is?</i>

48:43.380 --> 48:46.014
This is his brother Peel.

48:46.016 --> 48:48.150
And it's 5:47 a.m.

48:50.021 --> 48:52.389
WOMAN: <i>He doesn't have
a brother named Peel.</i>

48:54.323 --> 48:56.226
Are you sure?

48:57.727 --> 49:00.227
WILL [ON PHONE, SIGHS]:
<i>Jesus, Sarah. Who is it?</i>

49:00.229 --> 49:03.163
SARAH: <i>Some guy,
says he's your brother.</i>

49:03.165 --> 49:04.733
WILL: <i>Just give it...
Give it to me.</i>

49:05.768 --> 49:06.703
<i>Sam?</i>

49:08.270 --> 49:10.170
William?

49:10.172 --> 49:12.273
WILL:
<i>Uh. Yeah?</i>

49:14.476 --> 49:16.278
It's me, Peel.

49:18.246 --> 49:20.314
WILL:
<i>H-hold... Hold on.</i>

49:20.316 --> 49:24.685
<i>I gotta... I gotta
take this. Um...</i>

49:24.687 --> 49:27.253
<i>Peel, how did you...?
How did you get my number?</i>

49:27.255 --> 49:29.422
It was on my
roommate's computer.

49:29.424 --> 49:32.528
WILL:
<i>Oh, uh... Well...</i>

49:34.195 --> 49:36.529
<i>It's good to hear
your voice, Peel,</i>

49:36.531 --> 49:39.265
<i>but it's kind of early.</i>

49:39.267 --> 49:41.736
I got so excited.
I couldn't wait.

49:44.073 --> 49:46.104
WILL:
<i>Uh... Uh...</i>

49:46.106 --> 49:48.506
- <i>Yeah, um...</i>
- Mom is dead.

49:48.508 --> 49:49.811
WILL:
<i>What?</i>

49:51.346 --> 49:53.278
<i>Mom died?</i>

49:53.280 --> 49:54.649
<i>When?</i>

49:55.483 --> 49:57.382
Last month.

49:57.384 --> 49:58.786
WILL:
<i>Shit.</i>

50:02.356 --> 50:04.458
Do you still live with Dad?

50:05.759 --> 50:08.326
WILL:
<i>Um... No. Um...</i>

50:08.328 --> 50:10.664
<i>Dad died
a while back, Peel.</i>

50:12.667 --> 50:14.132
Dad's dead?

50:14.134 --> 50:15.769
WILL:
<i>Yeah, Dad... Dad's dead.</i>

50:17.370 --> 50:20.839
<i>You didn't know?
Mom never told you?</i>

50:20.841 --> 50:23.409
No, she never said anything.

50:26.380 --> 50:28.245
What about Sam?

50:28.247 --> 50:30.383
Is Sam still alive?

50:32.119 --> 50:33.584
WILL:
<i>As far as I know,</i>

50:33.586 --> 50:36.389
<i>but I haven't
talked to him in a while.</i>

50:39.258 --> 50:40.858
SARAH:
<i>Who is that?</i>

50:40.860 --> 50:44.495
WILL: <i>Just hold on.
I'll be out in a second.</i>

50:44.497 --> 50:47.463
<i>Listen, Peel, I gotta go.</i>

50:47.465 --> 50:49.466
<i>It was good talking to you,</i>

50:49.468 --> 50:52.838
<i>but hopefully we'll get
the chance to talk again.</i>

50:54.506 --> 50:56.540
<i>Take care, all right?</i>

50:56.542 --> 50:58.541
- [PHONE HITS CRADLE]
- [LINE BUZZING]

50:58.543 --> 50:59.844
Hello?

51:01.747 --> 51:03.281
William?

51:13.191 --> 51:14.926
[♪♪♪]

51:45.556 --> 51:46.957
[DOOR CLOSES]

51:49.326 --> 51:52.695
[SIGHS] Can you give me a
ride to the bus station?

51:55.699 --> 51:56.967
Sure.

52:38.573 --> 52:39.908
Can I help you?

52:41.009 --> 52:42.910
I'm here to see William.

52:42.912 --> 52:44.613
He's not here.

52:45.947 --> 52:47.681
Do you know when
he'll be back?

52:49.718 --> 52:52.353
Can I ask
what this is about?

52:54.823 --> 52:56.555
It's okay.

52:56.557 --> 52:58.459
I'll just wait.

53:11.705 --> 53:13.041
[DOOR OPENS]

53:16.609 --> 53:20.913
Uh, Will called.
He's on his way home.

53:20.915 --> 53:23.783
He wanted me to ask
if your name is Peel?

53:24.485 --> 53:26.617
Okay.

53:26.619 --> 53:30.656
Okay, so are you Peel?

53:30.658 --> 53:32.523
Yeah.

53:32.525 --> 53:33.858
Good.

53:33.860 --> 53:36.829
I'm Will's wife,
Sarah.

53:36.831 --> 53:39.032
Can I use your bathroom?

53:41.801 --> 53:44.971
He's playing with the girls.
It's fine.

53:45.972 --> 53:47.073
I don't know.

53:48.842 --> 53:52.644
He brought a suitcase
and a piece of wood.

53:54.046 --> 53:56.615
Calm down, Will.
It's okay.

53:57.783 --> 53:59.049
Strawberry volcano.

53:59.051 --> 54:00.787
[GIGGLING]

54:02.387 --> 54:04.790
Peel, can I get you
something to drink?

54:07.026 --> 54:09.394
Do you have any Oran-Zini?

54:11.729 --> 54:13.797
Actually, we do.

54:13.799 --> 54:15.497
[DOOR OPENS]

54:15.499 --> 54:18.435
- MOLLY: Daddy's home.
- ASHLEY: Daddy's home.

54:18.437 --> 54:20.837
- MOLLY: Hey, Daddy.
- ASHLEY: Hey, Daddy.

54:20.839 --> 54:22.571
Hey. Hey.

54:22.573 --> 54:25.443
What's up, girls? Huh?

54:35.385 --> 54:37.020
Um...

54:37.022 --> 54:39.989
My loves, how about you go play
out back for a little while

54:39.991 --> 54:41.924
while Peel catches up
with Daddy, okay?

54:41.926 --> 54:43.427
Okay.

54:51.135 --> 54:52.600
[EXHALES]

54:52.602 --> 54:53.970
Peel.

54:54.839 --> 54:56.506
Um...

54:57.707 --> 54:58.808
Wow, you...

55:00.043 --> 55:02.545
You look almost
exactly the same.

55:03.680 --> 55:04.714
You don't.

55:06.483 --> 55:09.150
Yeah, well, uh...

55:09.152 --> 55:10.785
[CHUCKLES]

55:10.787 --> 55:12.122
Um...

55:14.024 --> 55:15.790
So you're here.

55:15.792 --> 55:18.428
You showed up.

55:20.730 --> 55:21.664
You, um...

55:23.899 --> 55:26.669
You gonna
build something?

55:27.803 --> 55:29.071
I wanna measure you.

55:31.740 --> 55:33.108
[SCOFFS]

55:35.744 --> 55:36.879
It's Dad's...

55:38.080 --> 55:39.480
...measuring board.

55:40.983 --> 55:42.718
Wha...?

55:44.420 --> 55:45.955
Really? That's...

55:47.089 --> 55:48.989
That's... That's wild.

55:48.991 --> 55:50.489
[CHUCKLES]

55:50.491 --> 55:51.991
Can I?

55:51.993 --> 55:56.562
Eh... No, no. I'm gonna
go get ready, change...

55:56.564 --> 55:58.798
Honey, come on.

55:58.800 --> 55:59.932
[SCOFFS]
I'm not gonna...

55:59.934 --> 56:01.734
Come on. Let's see
how tall you are.

56:01.736 --> 56:03.037
[GROANS]

56:05.139 --> 56:06.941
All right. Fine.

56:09.811 --> 56:11.112
Okay.

56:14.849 --> 56:16.715
Interesting.

56:16.717 --> 56:17.784
What?

56:21.488 --> 56:23.121
You're 6 feet tall.

56:23.123 --> 56:24.724
[LAUGHS]

56:24.726 --> 56:27.159
No, that's...

56:27.161 --> 56:29.861
That can't be right.
I was 6'1" in high school.

56:29.863 --> 56:32.030
- It's...
- You shrunk.

56:32.032 --> 56:33.765
WILL:
Yeah.

56:33.767 --> 56:35.033
Uh, maybe.

56:35.035 --> 56:36.601
Um...

56:36.603 --> 56:39.639
Well, thank you for
measuring me. That was...

56:40.873 --> 56:42.542
...different.

56:44.478 --> 56:46.710
Does Sam live
around here?

56:46.712 --> 56:48.813
No. No.

56:48.815 --> 56:51.851
Last time I talked to Sam,
he was in Biloxi.

56:52.818 --> 56:53.786
When was that?

56:54.788 --> 56:56.023
A few years ago.

56:57.590 --> 56:59.790
We don't really
keep in touch, you know?

56:59.792 --> 57:02.659
Things haven't
gone so well for Sam.

57:02.661 --> 57:07.097
He's had a drug problem,
on and off, since high school.

57:07.099 --> 57:08.801
Do you have
his phone number?

57:10.002 --> 57:12.101
I need to
ask him something.

57:12.103 --> 57:16.572
No. I mean, even I did,
he wouldn't wanna talk to you.

57:16.574 --> 57:19.045
He doesn't want anything
to do with his family.

57:27.552 --> 57:33.289
So, what have you
been up to...

57:33.291 --> 57:35.058
the last 25 years?

57:35.060 --> 57:36.594
Well...

57:38.596 --> 57:41.598
the day after you left,
I felt really bad.

57:42.801 --> 57:45.936
So I went into my room
and cried.

57:49.706 --> 57:51.942
And then
the day after that...

57:56.147 --> 57:58.615
I don't really remember.

58:01.319 --> 58:03.151
I mean,
you don't have to give me

58:03.153 --> 58:05.853
a whole day-to-day account.
I just...

58:05.855 --> 58:09.623
I just meant,
how have you been lately?

58:09.625 --> 58:11.195
Oh.

58:12.161 --> 58:13.762
Good, I guess.

58:13.764 --> 58:15.132
[DOOR OPENS]

58:16.567 --> 58:19.568
- You boys doing okay?
- Yeah. We're good.

58:19.570 --> 58:22.269
Okay.
The girls are asleep.

58:22.271 --> 58:25.273
They wanted me to tell you,
"Good night, Uncle Peel."

58:25.275 --> 58:26.974
Good night.

58:26.976 --> 58:30.913
Got some pillows
and blankets out for you.

58:32.583 --> 58:34.150
Glad you're here.

58:36.051 --> 58:37.720
Sleep well.

58:45.194 --> 58:47.162
Why did Dad leave?

58:48.931 --> 58:50.932
I don't know, Peel.

58:52.634 --> 58:56.339
I mean, I wish things
were different. I really do.

58:59.707 --> 59:01.977
Why didn't
he take me with him?

59:02.878 --> 59:04.310
I...

59:04.312 --> 59:06.181
It wasn't like that.

59:07.349 --> 59:08.750
Listen, I, uh...

59:10.152 --> 59:13.786
I'm glad you came to visit,
I am, but it's late.

59:13.788 --> 59:16.924
You know?
And I got a big day tomorrow.

59:18.293 --> 59:19.827
Okay.

59:21.061 --> 59:23.297
I just don't understand.

59:26.066 --> 59:27.668
[SIGHS]

59:29.270 --> 59:32.206
Dad did not leave
because of you.

59:34.175 --> 59:38.745
Dad left because he thought
Mom was a nutcase.

59:40.114 --> 59:43.649
I mean, they had problems,
Peel. They...

59:43.651 --> 59:45.250
They couldn't get along.

59:45.252 --> 59:48.887
And Dad, you know,
he was just... He was just...

59:48.889 --> 59:51.789
He just wasn't available,
and he just shut down.

59:51.791 --> 59:54.994
And Mom,
she felt completely alone...

59:56.363 --> 59:58.198
...and she poured
everything into us.

59:59.432 --> 01:00:02.033
And it was...
It was excessive.

01:00:02.035 --> 01:00:04.202
He didn't like the way
she was raising us.

01:00:04.204 --> 01:00:08.172
With the homeschooling
and the breastfeeding.

01:00:08.174 --> 01:00:13.044
I mean, I don't even wanna know
how long she breastfed you.

01:00:13.046 --> 01:00:14.713
Until I was 10.

01:00:16.449 --> 01:00:19.250
Uh... No. Don't...

01:00:19.252 --> 01:00:22.085
Don't ever tell anybody that.

01:00:22.087 --> 01:00:23.786
Ever.

01:00:23.788 --> 01:00:27.023
Hell, you think
you had it hard living with Mom?

01:00:27.025 --> 01:00:30.061
I mean, you probably had it
a lot easier than me and Sam.

01:00:31.897 --> 01:00:36.166
Dad just... He hated himself
and he took it out on us.

01:00:36.168 --> 01:00:38.136
Especially Sam.

01:00:39.837 --> 01:00:42.374
Why didn't he ever come see me?

01:00:44.142 --> 01:00:45.442
[SIGHS]

01:00:45.444 --> 01:00:47.476
He wanted to.

01:00:47.478 --> 01:00:50.382
He never called me
or anything.

01:00:54.919 --> 01:00:56.354
Here, um...

01:00:58.222 --> 01:01:02.059
Just hold on a second, okay?
I'll be right back.

01:01:21.911 --> 01:01:23.912
[SIGHS]

01:01:29.019 --> 01:01:30.820
[SIGHS]

01:01:32.856 --> 01:01:36.293
Over the years,
Dad wrote you letters.

01:01:37.861 --> 01:01:39.262
He, uh...

01:01:40.829 --> 01:01:44.198
He felt so guilty,
you know, about leaving.

01:01:44.200 --> 01:01:47.868
But he could just never get
the courage up to mail them,

01:01:47.870 --> 01:01:50.806
so they just... They just
piled up in the box.

01:01:51.775 --> 01:01:53.242
Um...

01:01:54.477 --> 01:01:56.443
I think he hoped that

01:01:56.445 --> 01:01:59.146
someday when you're
a little older, you know,

01:01:59.148 --> 01:02:01.048
he could give them
to you in person.

01:02:01.050 --> 01:02:02.215
[CLEARS THROAT]

01:02:02.217 --> 01:02:04.852
I know he'd want you
to have them.

01:02:09.458 --> 01:02:12.027
All right. Um,
I'm gonna get some sleep.

01:02:14.028 --> 01:02:15.531
Come home.

01:02:17.231 --> 01:02:19.168
[SIGHS]
Peel...

01:02:22.403 --> 01:02:24.204
[SIGHS]

01:02:24.206 --> 01:02:26.105
Listen, I am...
I'm really...

01:02:26.107 --> 01:02:29.140
I'm glad you came
to visit. I am.

01:02:29.142 --> 01:02:31.377
But, you know, I got
a lot going on right now,

01:02:31.379 --> 01:02:34.280
a lot of, uh,
stuff at work.

01:02:34.282 --> 01:02:36.015
Just a lot. Um...

01:02:36.017 --> 01:02:37.485
I can't really handle...

01:02:38.852 --> 01:02:41.186
a lot right now,
so, um...

01:02:41.188 --> 01:02:43.322
Yeah, I think it'd be best
if you, you know,

01:02:43.324 --> 01:02:45.359
just head home
in the morning.

01:02:48.995 --> 01:02:50.397
Okay.

01:02:52.265 --> 01:02:55.536
Do you think maybe we could
get pancakes in the morning?

01:02:56.536 --> 01:02:58.203
Yeah.

01:02:58.205 --> 01:03:00.972
I mean, it's a little crazy
around here with the girls,

01:03:00.974 --> 01:03:04.242
getting them ready for school
and everything...

01:03:04.244 --> 01:03:06.980
but I mean,
we could definitely try.

01:03:10.216 --> 01:03:12.484
Okay.

01:03:12.486 --> 01:03:14.452
[WHISPERING] I can't believe
you're kicking him out.

01:03:14.454 --> 01:03:15.854
[WHISPERING]
I'm not kicking him out.

01:03:15.856 --> 01:03:18.123
He's your little brother.

01:03:18.125 --> 01:03:21.959
I'm aware of that.
I'm not kicking him out, Sarah.

01:03:21.961 --> 01:03:25.262
I mean, I have a lot going on
right now. I can't handle this.

01:03:25.264 --> 01:03:29.031
"A lot going on"?
You always have a lot going on.

01:03:29.033 --> 01:03:32.436
He is your brother, Will.
Your flesh and blood.

01:03:32.438 --> 01:03:35.171
[SCOFFS]
I haven't seen him in 25 years.

01:03:35.173 --> 01:03:37.541
You think it's easy
to pick up where we left off?

01:03:37.543 --> 01:03:39.443
Like everything's
okay and wonderful?

01:03:39.445 --> 01:03:41.477
You have no idea
what this has been like.

01:03:41.479 --> 01:03:44.313
I have no idea because you never
even fucking told me he existed.

01:03:44.315 --> 01:03:45.982
[NORMALLY]
He's gonna hear you.

01:03:45.984 --> 01:03:48.017
SARAH: He overhears me?
I hope he hears me.

01:03:48.019 --> 01:03:50.219
WILL: Sarah,
you're gonna wake the kids.

01:03:50.221 --> 01:03:52.288
SARAH: Fine.
Maybe you can explain to them

01:03:52.290 --> 01:03:54.358
why their daddy sent
their new uncle home.

01:03:54.360 --> 01:03:56.159
WILL:
Don't make me be the bad guy.

01:03:56.161 --> 01:03:57.493
I'm not the one
who showed up

01:03:57.495 --> 01:03:59.395
on someone's doorstep
out of the blue.

01:03:59.397 --> 01:04:01.230
I mean,
it's a lot to process.

01:04:01.232 --> 01:04:03.568
It's a big thing.
It's a big adjustment.

01:04:05.436 --> 01:04:07.969
SARAH: Well,
maybe while you're adjusting,

01:04:07.971 --> 01:04:12.108
you can process why the hell
you are so goddamn closed off.

01:04:12.110 --> 01:04:14.109
Just like your dad.

01:04:14.111 --> 01:04:15.544
[♪♪♪]

01:04:15.546 --> 01:04:17.579
[SCOFFS]

01:04:17.581 --> 01:04:19.617
I'm nothing like him.

01:05:16.338 --> 01:05:18.474
Hey there, world traveler.

01:05:19.976 --> 01:05:21.343
Where's Chad?

01:05:25.213 --> 01:05:28.550
Couldn't make it.
Cheerleader practice.

01:05:35.523 --> 01:05:37.225
How was Georgia?

01:05:40.996 --> 01:05:44.098
It's like Alabama,
but Georgia.

01:05:45.000 --> 01:05:46.333
What's with the board?

01:05:48.770 --> 01:05:50.504
You're not still
mad at me, are you?

01:05:52.506 --> 01:05:55.342
Peel, I really did think
it was Jooeun.

01:06:08.522 --> 01:06:10.590
You just gonna sit there?

01:06:19.667 --> 01:06:22.333
You think this car
could make it to Biloxi?

01:06:22.335 --> 01:06:24.270
[♪♪♪]

01:06:32.679 --> 01:06:36.213
<i>♪ Down that dusty road ♪</i>

01:06:36.215 --> 01:06:39.750
Biloxi? I can't believe
you've never been.

01:06:39.752 --> 01:06:41.819
I go at least
every month.

01:06:41.821 --> 01:06:44.220
Why? Can you bet on
horses there?

01:06:44.222 --> 01:06:47.524
Sure you can.
Why do you ask?

01:06:47.526 --> 01:06:49.760
Isn't that what
you and Chuck do?

01:06:49.762 --> 01:06:52.329
Make bets with horses?

01:06:52.331 --> 01:06:54.199
We're investors.
I told you that.

01:06:55.667 --> 01:06:59.702
My brother told me that
a trifecta is a horse's bet.

01:06:59.704 --> 01:07:02.539
Oh, yeah?
Well, amigo,

